headline: Centene Faces HBR Pressures: Will Scale Support Stability?
summary: CNC's rising HBR, driven by higher medical costs and policy shifts, pressures margins as it leans on scale and efficiency for stability.

headline: Centene (CNC) Valuation in Focus After Class Action Lawsuits and Pulled 2025 Guidance
summary: If you own shares of Centene (CNC), recent headlines may have given you pause. A series of class action lawsuits have been filed against the company, alleging that Centene misrepresented key facts about its Medicare business. Investors are now considering the implications, especially after Centene withdrew its 2025 financial guidance. The company cited an actuarial review that revealed weaker market growth and higher-than-expected morbidity levels, which has shaken confidence and sent the...
